THE family of madala Tawana is in need of help. This is because Tawana Thoka (76) went missing last Tuesday.The old man allegedly went out and told his family he was going out for some air, but never returned. Now the family from Batho Kasi in Mangaung fear the worst. Police spokeswoman Sergeant Ikobeng Hlobi said: “ At the time of his disappearance, madala Tawana was wearing a navy blue V-neck jersey and pants, long sleeve black and white shirt, and black shoes. If you have seen him, contact your nearest police station or Warrant Officer John Majolo, on 051 409 7341/13 or 073 882 1330.”